<CDLItem itemNbr="57-25-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.CDL.3-57-25-03.1.3-57-25-03">
<Title>Wing-Body Fairing Flap Door Seal</Title>
<DispatchCondition>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>Any amount of seal may be missing. When any portion of seal is missing, the corresponding door must be removed and the landing gear must remain extended for the first 10 minutes after takeoff and the penalties shown below should also be applied.</Para>
<Para>Procedure:
Do not retract landing gear for 10 minutes after takeoff. In the event of an engine failure after V1, retract the landing gear until a minimum of 1,500 feet above airport elevation and terrain clearance is assured. While maintaining terrain clearance, extend the gear for the balance of the 10 minutes.</Para>
<Para>Reduce performance limited weights by:</Para>
